quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
27,77,"and it is a guidance and mercy for the believers. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
27,78,"Indeed your Lord will decide between them {1} by His judgement. He is All-Mighty, All-Knowing.",footnotes:1:“Between them”: Between the disbelievers of the Quraish and the believers.
27,79,"So {1} put your trust in Allah for you are on the manifest truth.",footnotes:1:That is
27,80,"Surely you cannot make the dead hear you, {1} nor can you make the deaf hear your call if they turn back in flight, {2}",footnotes:1:That is
27,81,"nor can you direct the blind to the Right Way, {1} preventing them from falling into error. You can make only those who believe in Our verses to hear the call and then submit.",footnotes:1:That is
27,82,"And when the time for the fulfilment of Our Word against them will come, {1} We shall bring forth for them a beast from the earth who will speak to them because people did not believe in Our Signs. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
27,83,"Just imagine the Day when We shall muster from every nation a large group of those who gave the lie to Our Signs, and they shall be duly arranged in ranks"
27,84,"until, when all of them have arrived,"Allah will say: "Did you give the lie to My Signs even without encompassing them with your knowledge? {1} If that is not so", what did you do?"<sup foot_note="179941">2</sup>",footnotes:1:That is
27,85,"And the Word will come to pass against them because of their wrong-doing: they will then be able to utter nothing."
27,86,"Did they not perceive that We had made the night so that they may repose in it and made the day clear and shining. {1} Surely there are Signs in this for those who believe. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
27,87,"The Day when the Trumpet will be blown all those who are in the heavens and on the earth shall be terror stricken {1} - all except those whom Allah wills - and everyone shall come to Him utterly abject.",footnotes:1:For a detailed discussion of the blowing of the Trumpet
27,88,"You now see the mountains and consider them firmly fixed, but then they shall pass away even as clouds pass away. That will be the handiwork of Allah Who has created everything with perfect wisdom. He is well aware of what you do. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
